            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Xihuitl tlen ce tlamantli zacatl huan xihuitl tlen quence cencah. Nouhquiya, motequihuia para momanextiz ce tlamanti xihuitl, xihuitl tlen quicuah tecuanimeh tlen quicuah zacatl. Xihuimeh tlen inintzincuayo pilhuehhueyactzin huan yahyahualtic tlen gramineas huan xihuimeh tlen necih cencah tlen ni. Nouhquiya, nochi motequihuiya para momanextiz zacatl, zacatl tlen quicuah tecuanimeh, tecuanimeh tlen mopehuah.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>屬於禾本科的植物以及其他外觀上與之相似的植物。此外，通常亦會用於指稱牧草，尤其是草食動物所食用的糧草。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
